External Control.

This UM job can either run independantly (with optional resubmission
via the internal UM system for continuation runs) or be controlled
by an external system that is known to the UMUI.

The generalised Suite Control System (SCS) is the only registered
control system known to the UMUI.

If you choose this option you are defining this UM job as a component
within a suite controlled by the SCS.

Certain values will be specified externally and hence greyed out
in the UMUI. Other parameters, typically input and output files,
can be optionally defined as externally controlled. These will
appear red on the windows and you can define them as EXTERNAL
to have them controlled by the SCS, or give a valid response to
define the file yourself.

